[{'comment_id': 453369511, 'comment_body': 'You are mocking server call here right ?
So line 65, 66, 70 and 71 is basically mocking both success and error at same time which is not possible. In reality channel.post will run either function passed in as `success` param or as `error` param. Also this is not right way to trigger these.


', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 22, 13, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'thedeveloperr', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453369927, 'comment_body': "For success test case
```javascript
channel.post = function (req) {
            posted = true;
            assert.equal(req.url, url);
            assert.equal(req.data.csrfmiddlewaretoken, 'fake-csrf-token');
            assert.equal(req.data['file-0'], 'image1.png');
            assert.equal(req.data['file-1'], 'image2.png');
            // maybe add a delay here to simulate network request using setTimeout ? 
           //not sure I have never done this in zulip 
            req.success(); // simulate success server call
        };
```

For error test case:
```javascript
channel.post = function (req) {
            posted = true;
            assert.equal(req.url, url);
            assert.equal(req.data.csrfmiddlewaretoken, 'fake-csrf-token');
            assert.equal(req.data['file-0'], 'image1.png');
            assert.equal(req.data['file-1'], 'image2.png');
            // maybe add a delay here to simulate network request using setTimeout ? 
           //not sure I have never done this in zulip 
            req.error(); // simulate error server call, will trigger error codepath of function under test.
        };
```

Use both cases in separate test cases and separately. Don't call them together as you are doing in line 70 and 71", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 22, 18, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'thedeveloperr', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453370239, 'comment_body': 'Not sure of context but seeing your test and this code lines, I suggest to do in your channel.post mock code:
